Previous 3D spheroid experiments show that invasion occurs on a much faster time scale than reproduction [14]. By assuming that factors (V,P,N) and domains (ΩL,ΩF) change much faster than cell counts (equivalently γV,γP,γN,γOL,γOF ≫ rL,rF), one can reduce these equations to a set of two equations (L,F), where variables in Eqs (3)–(7) are at their equilibria




